"adj. 草书的 【英】 adj. 草书的(designating writing in which the strokes of the letters are joined in each word) 【记】 curs(跑)+ive→(写字 )像跑一样→草书的 【例】 Please use cursive script. Do not print. adj. 草书的(字母连在一起的) 【记】curs跑－字像跑一样－草书的 【记】current 水流 + 音：写文，象水流一样连续不断的写文章→草体字；running 流动的，源自run跑，流 【相关】cursive 草书的，cursor 游标，(计算机屏幕)光标，指针,discursive 含很多主题的，excursion旅行，excursive 跑题的，incursion 袭击，侵入，precursor 先驱，recursive 回归的，计算机剃归算法 cursive (adj.)  1784, from French cursif (18c.), from Medieval Latin cursivus ""running,"" from Latin cursus ""a running,"" from past participle of currere ""to run"" (see current (adj.)). The notion is of ""written with a running hand"" (without raising the pen), originally as opposed to the older uncial hand."
